elements.name: question1
elements.title: Would you rather be EFFICIENT or CAREFREE?
choices: Efficient - working in a well-organized and competent way.
Carefree - without anxiety or worry.

elements.name: question3
elements.title: Would you rather be ORGANIZED or FLEXIBLE?
choices: Organized - arranged in a systematic way.
Flexible - ready and able to change so as to adapt to different circumstances.

elements.name: question4
elements.title: Would you rather be THOROUGH or SPONTANEOUS?
choices: Thorough - attentive to accuracy and detail.
Spontaneous - having an open, natural, and uninhibited manner.

elements.name: question5
elements.title: Would you rather be DEPENDABLE or UNPREDICTABLE?
choices: Dependable - trustworthy and reliable.
Unpredictable - behaving in a way that is not easily predicted.

elements.name: question7
elements.title: Would you rather be COMPLEX or SIMPLE?
choices: Complex - consisting of many different and connected parts.
Simple - easily understood or done.

elements.name: question8
elements.title: Would you rather be OBVIOUS or SUBTLE?
choices: Obvious - easily perceived, apparent or clear.
Subtle - inconspicuous and understated.

elements.name: question10
elements.title: Would you rather be FLASHY or DISCREET?
choices: Flashy - ostentatiously attractive or impressive.
Discreet - intentionally unobtrusive.

elements.name: question12
elements.title: Would your rather be TALKATIVE or OBSERVANT?
choices: Talkative - fond of talking; socializing.
Observant - watchful; attentive.

elements.name: question13
elements.title: Would you rather be ENERGETIC or FAMILIAR?
choices: Energetic - involving great activity or vitality.
Familiar - associated in close personal relations.

elements.name: question14
elements.title: Would you rather be SOCIABLE or INDEPENDENT?
choices: Sociable - willing to talk and engage in activities with other people; friendly.
Independent - not influenced by the thought or action of others.

elements.name: question15
elements.title: Would you rather be AUTHORITATIVE or HELPFUL?
choices: Authoritative - commanding and self-confident; likely to be respected and obeyed.
Helpful - giving or ready to give aid or assistance.

elements.name: question16
elements.title: Would you rather be DIRECT or WARM?
choices: Direct - straightforward; frank.
Warm - showing affection or kindness.

elements.name: question17
elements.title: Would you rather be CAREFUL or CONSIDERATE?
choices: Careful - cautious in one's actions.
Considerate - showing kindly awareness or regard for another's feelings

elements.name: question18
elements.title: Would you rather be an EXPERT or COURTEOUS?
choices: Expert - having or involving authoritative knowledge.
Courteous - polite, respectful, or considerate in manner.

elements.name: question19
elements.title: Would you rather be PROFESSIONAL or FRIENDLY?
choices: Professional - a person who is expert at his or her work.
Friendly - kind and pleasant.
